# Age keys. The local-dev key is committed on purpose — it only decrypts
# clusters/local/* dev secrets on a localhost cluster, so shipping it removes
# the onboarding key handoff. Every OTHER environment's private key (prod,
# staging, …) must stay out of git: keep it in your homedir or a secrets
# manager. The allowlist below is exact, so a key dropped at the conventional
# clusters/<env>/age.key path can never be committed by accident.
clusters/*/age.key
!clusters/local/age.key
